2) There are several things that can be done, which have been done by the
 Fed recently as it has hit the ZLB.
 One is forward guidance which is setting market expectations in the long-run
 regarding the path of interest rates thus changing the current marginal
 rate of substitution between consumption in the current period.
 Another is to change the reserve requirement which has rarely been used.
 As well, under certain New Keynesian models we could argue that debt restructur
ing could also be used as an effective way of restoring aggregate demand.
