Debt matters even if Americans owe money to other Americans.
 The reason for this is that if consumers are highly indebted then they
 cannot spend money and as a result aggregate demand is depressed.
 This matters on an aggregate level since this depressed aggregate demand
 leads to low sales and as a result higher unemployment.
 Due to this, it really does not matter who owes who what, it simply matters
 if consumers are so indebted that they cannot actually spend money so that
 there are perverse effects on aggregate demand.
